[title]
Atlanta warstory - my first post!
[head]
<meta name="description" content="Atlanta warstory - my first post!" />
[page]
		
<p>This is my first post on Smogon. My name is David and I was the winner of the Atlanta VGC event last weekend.</p>	
<h3>Here is my story</h3>
<p>My family started the journey to Atlanta by waking up at around 4:30 in the morning so we would not get there too late at night. We had to take a 13 hour trip from Chicago. During the trip I did not stop asking my dad to battle and he did not want to as much because I have beaten all of his teams. We made it to Atlanta at around 8:00 at night while enduring heavy rain along the way. We ate at the hotel, saw some of the Pokemon staff and then went to bed. </p>
<p>We woke up at 6:00 to get ready. My sister was in the juniors so we had to get up early. She ended up winning the junior division. While she was in her top four my brother, my dad, and I got in line for the senior division. We sat in line for about 1 and a half hour. My team was as following:</p>

<div><img src="/download/sprites/dp/382.png" alt="Kyogre"/></div>
